    teaching: "Nietzsche's formula for greatness: not merely to tolerate what happens but to love it as necessary. The Stoics understood this too — Marcus Aurelius returning again and again to the discipline of wanting what occurs. On a trip this finds you whether you invite it or not: the weather that changes everything, the injury that slows you, the wrong turn that leads somewhere better. Amor fati is not resignation. It is the discovery that what resists you is also what shapes you. The obstacle is not in the way. It is the way.",
